'''Joh's New and Used Droid Emporium''' was a successful [[Droid/Legends|droid]] retail business operating in the [[Cularin system/Legends|Cularin system]]. It had a stall at the [[Cularin Trade Show]]. It also had another one in [[Genarius]], active during the [[SoroSuub Anniversary celebration, 31 BBY]].<ref name="BW">''[[Blown Away]]'' (as described in [https://web.archive.org/web/20021218152817/www.wizards.com/rpga/livingforce/article.asp?x=lf/swlf20010927b_transmissions&c=swlfc Transmissions From the Living Force Campaign] on the [[Wikipedia:Internet Archive#Wayback machine|Way back machine]])</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
Joh's existed both within [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] and as a metaorganization for the [[Living Force (roleplaying campaign)|Living Force]] campaign. Players in the Living Force were not allowed to just buy droids, they had to submit a request to Joh's, which would issue a certificate for the droid with a unique personality. Characters were allowed only one droid, and only characters with a certain level in the soldier class could buy a [[Battle droid/Legends|battle droid]]. Later in the campaign, the restrictions were loosened&mdash;characters could buy uncerted droids without going through Joh's, and if they owned a ship with a [[Astromech socket/Legends|droid socket]], they could own an [[Astromech droid/Legends|astromech]] in addition to one other droid.

